      ${
        sincnlem.5 $e |- A e. CC $.
        sincnlem.6 $e |- A =/= 0 $.
        sincnlem.7 $e |- C = ( abs o. - ) $.
        sincnlem.8 $e |- D = { <. <. p , q >. , r >. |
                               ( ( p e. ( CC X. CC ) /\ q e. ( CC X. CC ) ) /\
          r = sup ( { ( ( 1st ` p ) C ( 1st ` q ) ) ,
                      ( ( 2nd ` p ) C ( 2nd ` q ) ) } , RR , < ) ) } $.
        sincnlem.9 $e |- O e. ( ( Open ` D ) Cn ( Open ` C ) ) $.
        $( Lemma for ~ sincn and ~ coscn . $)
        sincnlem $p |- ( J o. H ) e. ( CC -cn-> CC ) $=
          ( ccom copn cfv ccn co cc ccncf wcel ce ci axicn mulc1cncf ax-mp
          eqid cncfmet1 eleqtr efcn cme w3a wa cnmet 3pm3.2i metcnco mpan
          mp2an cneg negcl cnmetba oprcn cc0 wne divccncf eleqtrr ) KJUEZFUFUGZ
          VSUHUIZUJUJUKUIZJVTULZKVTULZVRVTULZUMHUEZVTULZUMIUEZVTULZWBHVTULZUMVT
